item.title: CVE-2024-6045|2024-06-24T13:16:42.373Z -- d-link -- g403
item.description: Certain models of D-Link wireless routers contain an undisclosed factory testing backdoor. Unauthenticated attackers on the local area network can force the device to enable Telnet service by accessing a specific URL and can log in by using the administrator credentials obtained from analyzing the firmware.

item.title: CVE-2024-6044|2024-06-18T14:25:43.368Z -- d-link -- g403
item.description: Certain models of D-Link wireless routers have a path traversal vulnerability. Unauthenticated attackers on the same local area network can read arbitrary system files by manipulating the URL.
